```json
&quot;LogGroupName&quot;: {
    &quot;Fn::Join&quot;: [
        &quot;&quot;,
        [
            &quot;/aws/lambda/&quot;,
            {
                &quot;Ref&quot;: &quot;MyLambdaFunction&quot;
            }
        ]
    ]
}
```

Note that `MyLambdaFunction` is the name of your Lambda function block in the CloudFormation template.

The way [Serverless][1] does it should work for you. It creates a log group resource with a name matching what your Lambda function will use. You can then reference that log group wherever you need it. You will have to give your Lambda function a name and not use the default naming behavior. You can use the stack name to make it unique.

